I {{nihongo|'''Katsushika Hokusai'''|葛飾 北斎|extra=Setiembre 23, 1760&nbsp;– Mayo 10, 1849}}<ref name="nagata"/> metung yang Hapon a artist, pintor [[ukiyo-e]], ampong gágawang [[print]], ning panaun a  [[panauan a Edo]]. Meimpluwensiya ya kareng pintor antimo i [[Sesshu]], at aliwang uri ning [[pamaminturang Isik]].<ref name="csuchico"/>  Mibait ya king [[Edo]] (ngeni Tokyo), i Hokusai, a pekakilala antimong ginawa king serye da reng [[woodblock printing in Japan|woodblock print]] a {{Nihongo|''[[Atlung Pulu't Anam a Bista ning Bunduk Fuji]]''|富嶽三十六景|Fugaku Sanjūroku-kei|c. 1831}} nung nu ya kayabe ing kikilalanan king mabilug a yatung limbag a ''[[Ing Maragul a Alun Bandang Kanagawa]]'', (The Great Wave off Kanagawa) a melalang anyang dekadang 1820.

Lelangan neng Hokusai ing "Atlung pulu't anam a bista"  antimong pakibat king pangasikat ning pamaglakbe o turismong lokal, ampong metung a personal a matimid a hilig king [[Bunduk Fuji]].<ref name="smith"/> Yapin ing seryeng iti,  lalu na ing limbag a ''Ing Maragul a Alun'' ampo ing ''Fuji in Clear Weather'', a ganap a migpasikat kang Hokusai king Hapon ampo kareng aliwang bangsa. Anti ing sinabing ning talasulat amlat o historian a i [[Richard Douglas Lane|Richard Lane]], "Tutu pin, nung ating metung a obrang ginawa king lagyu nang Hokusai, king Hapon man o king kilwal na niti, ya pin iting mapyang serye da reng limbag...".<, "Indeed, if there is one work that made Hokusai's name, both in Japan and abroad, it must be this monumental print-series...".<ref name="lane"/> Kabang maulaga ing obra nang Hokusai bayu ing seryeng iti, e menikwang maleparan a pamangilala ampong miglakwan pangmalwatan a pamana king yatu ning arte o kalalangan anggang e linwal iti.' Yapin muring ing ''Ing Maragul a Alun'' a tinanggap, at tatanggap pa muring papuri ampong kasikatan king labwad ning Albugan. [[File:Great Wave off Kanagawa2.jpg|thumb|left|''[[Ing Maragul a Alun]]'', ing pekakilalang limbag nang Hokusai, ing mumuna king serye da reng ''Atlung Pulu't Anam a Bista ning Bunduk Fuji'']] 

